<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Heretic" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Heretic,</orth> one who holds opinions differing from the established faith: <bibl n="shak. son 124.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 124, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.4.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 4, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.236" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 236</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.175" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 175</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 84</bibl> (the indef. art. before it never <emph>a,</emph> but <emph>an</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>